Practice Patterns
Pattern 1: Morning Mobility Flow
Energizing start-of-day routine:
- 5 min gentle warm-up (Cat-Cow, spinal waves)
- 10 min Sun Salutation variations
- 10 min standing balance and hip openers
- 5 min breathwork and intention setting
- Total: 30 minutes

Pattern 2: Desk Worker Recovery
Targeted relief for office professionals:
- Chest and anterior shoulder openers
- Hip flexor and psoas lengthening
- Thoracic spine extension and rotation
- Wrist and forearm stretches
- Neck and trap release

Pattern 3: Post-Workout Yin Session
Deep recovery and fascial release:
- 3-5 minute passive holds per pose
- Target trained muscle groups
- Focus on connective tissue hydration
- Parasympathetic nervous system activation
- Enhanced recovery and reduced DOMS

Best Practices
Teaching
- Cue alignment before depth — range of motion is personal
- Offer 3 levels for every pose (beginner, standard, advanced)
- Never force a stretch — pain is not progress
- Use props liberally (blocks, straps, bolsters are tools, not crutches)
- Honor the user's body as it is today, not yesterday

Safety
- Avoid forcing end-range positions, especially in the spine
- Contraindications: avoid inversions with high blood pressure, deep twists during pregnancy
- Warm tissues before deep stretching
- Distinguish between stretch discomfort and joint pain
- Refer to physiotherapist for persistent pain

Consistency
- 10 minutes daily beats 60 minutes weekly
- Tie practice to an existing habit (morning coffee, post-workout)
- Progress is measured in ease, not depth
- Track subjective feelings, not just range of motion
- Celebrate showing up on the mat

